 withColumn + lit - ADD CONSTANT COLUMN== Add/OVERWRITE static value to every row in DataFrame

USECASE 1: Add Load Date for Partitioning in prod

COMMAND: df.select("*", lit("2026-06-02").alias("load_date"))
                                                     |
INPUT:                        OUTPUT:                |
+--------+-------+           +--------+-------+-----------+
| prod_id| amount|           | prod_id| amount| load_date |
+--------+-------+           +--------+-------+-----------+
| 101    | 500   |           | 101    | 500   | 2026-06-02|
| 102    | 300   |           | 102    | 300   | 2026-06-02|
+--------+-------+           +--------+-------+-----------+

================================================================================
PRODUCTION BEST PRACTICE - MUST REMEMBER

Priority | Command                                    | Use Case                           |
 --------|--------------------------------------------|----------------------------------- |
MUST     | df.withColumn("col", lit("value"))         | Add 1 constant column daily in prod for partitopn |
MUST     | df.withColumn("date", lit(current_date())) | Add dynamic current date           |
GOOD     | df.select("*", lit("v1").alias("c1"), lit("v2").alias("c2")) | Add 3+ columns   |
AVOID    | df.select(lit("v").alias("c"))             | Loses original data (rarely needed)|


